      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.03025",
      "snippet": "Forecasting future events as a testbed for general AI has drawn increasing attention. A natural way to materialize such evaluation is to have models trade in prediction markets. However, trading requires more than forecasting. Furthermore, recent benchmarks report a large gap between well-calibrated probability scores and trading outcomes. We propose Raven-Agent, the first autonomous trading agent for prediction markets, to our knowledge. In controlled replay on archived decision sets, our archi"
    },
    {
      "id": "arxiv-2607.05174",
