      "hebbian_credit": 10,
      "layer": "L8",
      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.04240",
      "snippet": "The transition of LLMs from passive generators to autonomous agents has introduced significant challenges in reliability, security, and state management. Current agentic architectures are often constructed ad-hoc, prone to hallucination cascades, infinite loops, and prompt injection attacks. This paper argues that many of these failure modes can be analyzed using control motifs long studied in systems biology. Five biological motifs are mapped to composable software design patterns: Coherent Fee"
    },
    {
      "id": "arxiv-2607.05202",
      "name": "EvoAgentBench: Benchmarking Agent Self-Evolution via Ability Transfer",
      "dir": "arxiv-2607.05202/",
      "source": "arXiv:cs.AI:2607.05202",
      "status": "digested",
