      "layer": "L8",
      "url": "",
      "snippet": "Personal agents will increasingly negotiate on behalf of users. Existing negotiation benchmarks emphasize agreement, surplus, or strategic competence, but a user-owned agent can reach an agreement while harming the user through privacy leakage, consent violation, unsupported advocacy, over-concession, failed escalation, or poor auditability. We introduce SovereignNegotiation-Bench, a trace-level multi-turn benchmark for delegated personal-agent negotiation under private utilities, disclosure con"
    },
    {
      "id": "answer-type-aware-llm-pipelines-for-bioasq-14b-wit",
      "name": "Answer-Type-Aware LLM Pipelines for BioASQ 14b with Self-Reflection and Multi-Agent",
      "dir": "answer-type-aware-llm-pipelines-for-bioasq-14b-wit/",
      "source": "arXiv:cs.CL:2607.new",
      "status": "digested",
      "added_at": "2026-07-18T12:30:01.205831+08:00",
      "digested_at": "2026-07-18T12:30:01.205831+08:00",
      "tags": [
        "self-reflection",
        "multi-agent"
      ],
      "score": 0.95,
      "hebbian_credit": 10,
      "layer": "L8",
      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.new",
      "snippet": "A question-type-specific LLM framework for BioASQ 14b. Uses self-reflection for yes/no questions and multi-agent architecture for list questions, selecting different inference procedures according to distinct reasoning and evaluation requirements for biomedical QA."
    },
    {
      "id": "decision-protocols-in-multi-agent-llm-conversation",
      "name": "Decision Protocols in Multi-Agent LLM Conversations",
      "dir": "decision-protocols-in-multi-agent-llm-conversation/",
      "source": "arXiv:cs.MA:2607.new",
      "status": "digested",
      "added_at": "2026-07-18T12:30:01.744148+08:00",
      "digested_at": "2026-07-18T12:30:01.744148+08:00",
      "tags": [
        "multi-agent",
        "cognitive architecture"
      ],
      "score": 0.95,
      "hebbian_credit": 10,
      "layer": "L8",
      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.ma.new1",
      "snippet": "Decision protocols are critical components of Multi-Agent Systems specifying how multiple agents collaborate to create a final solution. This paper systematically studies voting, consensus, and judge protocols on knowledge-intensive and logic-based datasets. Consensus suits knowledge tasks; voting and judge suit logic tasks. Independent generation diversity improves quality."
    },
    {
      "id": "delay-aware-active-triangulation-with-uncertainty-",
      "name": "Delay-Aware Active Triangulation with Uncertainty-Driven Multi-Agent RL for Counter-UAS",
      "dir": "delay-aware-active-triangulation-with-uncertainty-/",
      "source": "arXiv:cs.MA:2607.new",
      "status": "digested",
