      "snippet": "Proposes Statistically Meaningful Geometry (SMG) framework modeling overparametrized learning systems as infinite-dimensional nonparametric Orlicz fiber bundles. Proves that under sustained OOD stimulation, unmodeled variance leaks from visible horizontal base manifold into unobservable vertical fiber space, generating active non-causal tension. This triggers local volume collapse and matrix singularity, causing gauge symmetry breaking (GSB) that spontaneously crystallizes new independent horizo"
    },
    {
      "id": "arxiv-2607.07409",
      "name": "DeLS-Spec: Decoupled Long-Short Contexts for Parallel Speculative Drafting (2607.07409)",
      "dir": "arxiv-2607.07409/",
