      ],
      "score": 0.83,
      "hebbian_credit": 8,
      "layer": "L8",
      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.06855",
      "snippet": "On-policy distillation supplies dense teacher supervision on the student's own trajectories. We introduce GeoSD, a geometric self-distillation objective that treats drift as movement in the student's predictive behavior. A Hellinger loss scales each teacher preference by the overlap the student already shares with it, and a proximal term penalizes drift from a recent checkpoint measured as Fisher-Rao distance. Across mathematical reasoning benchmarks, GeoSD preserves in-distribution gains while "
    },
    {
      "id": "arxiv-2607.07517",
      "name": "Stability and Convergence of Optimistic Exponential Weights with Asymmetric Step Sizes in Bimatrix Games (2607.07517)",
