      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.08059",
      "snippet": "Uncertainty quantification for visual language models conventionally targets the answer token distribution. We provide the first three-family empirical characterisation of answer entropy behaviour in thinking-mode VLMs. Running four models on identical adversarial samples, we find three qualitatively distinct patterns: Qwen3-VL-8B-Thinking shows complete collapse; GLM-4.1V-9B-Thinking shows no collapse; and InternVL3-8B shows selective thinking on only 50% of samples."
