      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.08173",
      "snippet": "Black box auditing of language models may miss subtle forms of misalignment and hidden information. We introduce overthinking: the process of using reasoning task vectors to amplify the propensity to think out loud of reasoning models. Given non-reasoning instruct model M and reasoning-distilled model R, we define the overthinking model as theta_O_alpha = theta_M + alpha(theta_R - theta_M), where alpha > 1 amplifies reasoning beyond R. Additionally, we introduce layer-wise attenuation strategies"
    },
