      "hebbian_credit": 8,
      "layer": "L8",
      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2605.11404",
      "snippet": "This paper adapts Aumann-Shapley path-integral attribution to LLM-powered multi-agent systems at million-agent scale. The resulting method satisfies all four Shapley axioms, runs three to five orders of magnitude faster than sampled Shapley, and extends feasible axiomatic attribution by over three orders of magnitude (1670x). Applied to 14 days of Bluesky data (1,671,587 active users, five topics), it reveals that the long tail and middle tier jointly carry the majority, not the top influencers."
    },
