      "layer": "L8",
      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.09842",
      "snippet": "We investigate whether identity-specifying system prompts produce statistically distinguishable geometric fingerprints in the hidden-state trajectories of transformers spanning four post-training regimes. This relates to how models encode persistent self-identity across contexts."
    },
    {
      "id": "arxiv-2607.10197",
      "name": "GRATE: Temporal Extensions for Inductive KG Foundation Models via Gated Rotary Attention",
