      "hebbian_credit": 8,
      "layer": "L8",
      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.10197",
      "snippet": "Knowledge graph foundation models achieve strong inductive transfer by learning relation-graph representations that generalise to unseen entities and relations. Extending this transferability to temporal knowledge graphs remains challenging. We propose GRATE with gated rotary attention."
    },
    {
      "id": "arxiv-2607.09921",
      "name": "Global Merger-Arbitrage Forecasting with Language Models",
