      ],
      "score": 0.75,
      "hebbian_credit": 8,
      "layer": "L8",
      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.09765",
      "snippet": "A cheap swarm of unreliable agents can be steered to a correct consensus by a few strong expensive oracle correctors. We ask how much one must spend and where to place the oracles. We model the swarm as consensus on a graph with cost-coupled concave strength."
    },
    {
      "id": "arxiv-2607.09798",
      "name": "JEPA for AI-Native 6G: Predictive Representations and Open Challenges",
