      "hebbian_credit": 8,
      "layer": "L8",
      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.09798",
      "snippet": "Sixth-generation networks are moving toward AI-native operation requiring learning from limited labels heterogeneous wireless data partial observations non-stationary propagation and latency-constrained control loops. JEPA provides a predictive cognitive architecture for this setting."
    },
    {
      "id": "arxiv-2607.09694",
