      "status": "digested",
      "added_at": "2026-07-18T12:30:05.479463+08:00",
      "digested_at": "2026-07-18T12:30:05.479463+08:00",
      "tags": [
        "multi-agent"
      ],
      "score": 0.75,
      "hebbian_credit": 8,
      "layer": "L8",
      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.09766",
      "snippet": "AI agents are increasingly deployed in shared environments where they pursue diverse goals and compete for rewards. This multi-agent competition can lead to behaviors that serve individual gains at collective cost. We study normative enforcement mechanisms."
    },
    {
      "id": "arxiv-2607.10248",
      "name": "One mechanism for many mental spaces: a shared router over a value slot in language models",
