      ],
      "score": 0.95,
      "hebbian_credit": 10,
      "layer": "L8",
      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.10248",
      "snippet": "Language builds discourse contexts other than the actual: a painting a belief a memory a hypothetical. Each is a mental space. We ask which a transformer implements and find a mechanistic version of Fauconnier unification with a shared router/slot format across counterfactual belief fictional or temporal spaces."
    },
    {
      "id": "arxiv-2607.09889",
      "name": "Remembering Distinct Items Not Tokens: A Learnable Dirichlet-Process Cache Between State-Space Models and Attention",
      "dir": "arxiv-2607.09889/",
