      "tags": [
        "memory",
        "sparse-attention",
        "long-context"
      ],
      "score": 0.95,
      "hebbian_credit": 10,
      "layer": "L8",
      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.09889",
      "snippet": "Fixed-state sequence models compress an unbounded past into a bounded state capping associative recall at roughly state dimension. Attention escapes the cap at quadratic compute. We study the middle ground: a sparse cache that allocates a slot only when input is novel."
    },
    {
      "id": "arxiv-2607.09748",
      "name": "Replicating Belief, Not Bits: Epistemic State Replication for Agentic Systems",
      "dir": "arxiv-2607.09748/",
