      "hebbian_credit": 8,
      "layer": "L8",
      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.09685",
      "snippet": "Policy models often assume stability across institutional conditions. In adaptive socio-technical systems regulatory change can alter incentives and agents respond strategically. This paper studies such regime change as a transfer-learning problem in multi-agent settings."
    },
