      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.11995",
      "snippet": "We present a fine-tuned multi-agent framework for detecting the Big Five personality traits (OCEAN) from life narratives. The architecture decomposes trait detection into specialized subtasks handled by dedicated LLM agents, each fine-tuned on specific trait dimensions. Results demonstrate that the multi-agent decomposition approach outperforms monolithic classification baselines across all five trait dimensions, with particular advantage in detecting nuanced traits like openness and neuroticism"
    },
