      "snippet": "Reinforcement learning with verifiable rewards without human-annotated data, often referred to as zero RL, has emerged as a powerful paradigm for eliciting chain-of-thought reasoning. However, due to computational constraints, existing studies are largely restricted to small models. We present a stable and efficient training pipeline incorporating clipped importance sampling, training-inference ratio correction, and mixed-precision control. Key findings: (1) scaling to 1T parameters significantl"
    },
