      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2605.06676",
      "snippet": "Long-context inference in LLMs is bottlenecked by linear growth of KV cache memory. Existing KV cache compression paradigms are fundamentally limited by heuristics. To address this, we introduce LKV which formulates KV compression as an end-to-end differentiable optimization problem. LKV integrates LKV-H to learn task-optimized global budgets and LKV-T to derive intrinsic KV importance without materializing attention matrices. This design bypasses heuristic proxies, strictly aligning compression"
    },
